package enclavid:types;

/// Shared primitive types used across multiple interfaces. Kept in a
/// dedicated package so that consuming interfaces (disclosure, form,
/// future plugins) can `use` them without dragging in the semantic
/// definitions of the interface where they originated.
///
/// Why this matters: wit-bindgen's host-side trait generation treats
/// any interface whose types are `use`d elsewhere as "imported for
/// types" — even if the interface itself is purely exported. That
/// produced a spurious `Host` trait on the host side requiring a
/// dummy `unreachable!()` stub. Putting shared types in their own
/// pure-types interface (no functions) avoids the false-import
/// signal and lets `policy` interface be purely exported.
interface types {
    /// Reference to a string declared by the polici manifest's
    /// `disclosure_fields` (machine keys) or `localized` map
    /// (translatable UI strings). Opaque key — the host validates
    /// membership in the registered set at every use-site
    /// (`prompt-disclosure` field key/label, reason, media labels)
    /// and traps if absent. Format also enforced:
    /// `[a-z][a-z0-9_-]{0,127}` so the value is safe to display raw
    /// on the consent screen when surfaced for non-canonical keys.
    /// Type alias (not a record) so SDKs can compose constants
    /// cheaply: typically backed by a compile-time enum that
    /// surfaces a `&'static str` per entry.
    type text-ref = string;
}
